Name.Display: Sunix Serial and Parallel Card Driver

Description.Display: This package contains the Sunix Serial and Parallel Card driver. The Sunix Serial and Parallel card driver helps the system to communicate with the peripheral devices.

This package contains the NVIDIA GeForce GT640, GTX645, and GTX745 graphics driver. A graphics or video driver is the software that enables communication between the graphics card and the operating system, games, and applications.

Name.Display: Intel Rapid Storage Technology Driver and Management Console

Description.Display: Intel Rapid Storage Technology Driver and Management Console for OptiPlex 7020/9020M and Precision M2800 running the following Windows Operating Systems: Win 7, Win8, and Win 8.1.

This package contains the Realtek ALC269 High Definition audio driver. Audio driver is the software that helps your operating system to communicate with audio devices such as internal sound cards, speakers, headsets, and microphones.

This package contains the Dell system BIOS update. BIOS is a firmware that is embedded on a small memory chip on the system board. It controls the keyboard, monitor, disk drives, and other devices. This update addresses the Intel Security Advisory INTEL-SA-00115. A security advisory is a statement when a product is impacted by a security vulnerability and a remedy is available.

Name.Display: AMD Radeon HD 8490/8570 and R5 240/R7 250 Graphics Driver

Description.Display: This package contains the AMD Radeon HD 8490, 8570 and R5 240, R7 250 graphics driver. A graphics or video driver is the software that enables communication between the graphics card and the operating system, games, and applications.

This package contains the Intel Management Engine Components Installer. This driver installs Intel Management Engine Interface, Serial Over LAN driver, Local Manageability Service, Intel Converged Security and Manageability Engine (CSME), Windows Management Instrumentation (WMI) provider, Intel Management Security Status application, and Intel Capability Licensing Service Client. This update addresses the Intel Security Advisories INTEL-SA-00086 and INTEL-SA-00101. A security advisory is a statement when a security vulnerability impacts a product, and a remedy is available for the vulnerability. The chipset driver must be installed before installing this package.

Device.Display: Intel Unified AMT 8.1 WS Management Interface

Description.Display: This package contains the Intel chipset driver. The Chipset driver helps to install INF files in a system. The INF files are used in turn by the operating system for installation of software and drivers.
This package contains the remedy described in Remediation Step 1 of Dell Security Advisory DSA-2021-088. See Dell Security Advisory DSA-2021-088 for details.

This package provides Dell Command | Configure Application and is supported on Venue 11 Pro, XPS Notebook, OptiPlex, Precision and Latitude that are running the following Windows operating systems: Windows 10, Windows 8.1, Windows 8 and Windows 7.
This package contains the Dell Digital Delivery Application (or Alienware Digital Delivery Application). This application enables you to obtain software that you purchased with your system.

This package provides Dell Command | Monitor Application and is supported on Tablet, XPS, OptiPlex, Precision and Latitude that are running the following Windows operating systems: Windows 10, Windows 8.1 and Windows 7.

This package contains the Dell Command | Update application. Dell Command Update is a stand-alone application for client systems, that provides updates for system software that is released by Dell. This application simplifies the BIOS, firmware, driver, and application update experience for Dell client hardware.
